So maybe he's looking forward to better times.
From unofficial information, it seems that the first virtual operator should be here, perhaps by the end of the year.
But for now, his rise is accompanied by an impenetrable wall of silence.
'At the moment we do not believe that there is room for a full-fledged virtual operator on the Czech market.
The Czech market is very specific compared to other markets.
So far, no entity has approached us with a comprehensive and serious project in this area", said Vlastimil Sršeň from Telefónica O2's press department in a statement to Mobil.cz.
Other operators also refer to the specificity of the Czech market.
T-Mobile spokeswoman Martina Kemr agrees with O2: 'We have not yet seen any viable and mutually beneficial business project on which to build.'
He adds: "It is unlikely that a virtual operator will appear on the T-Mobile network before the end of the year.
