'The Authority has found no evidence of anti-competitive conduct in this case and therefore has no reason to intervene in any way.
None of the operators has a dominant position and therefore no correspondingly increased responsibility for its market behaviour.
The telecoms regulator is also likely to lack the necessary tools to open up the mobile market to virtual operators,' Chalupa said in a statement.
The interpretation of the dominant position is one of the many points of dispute.
There is of course an analysis of the relevant markets by the CTU which shows that telecommunications is the only market from a competitive point of view.
